race.comment: LIFT'N'MEHIGHER (10) conceded a big start from a wide gate and was never a chance over 1350m at Doomben. She was a big maiden winner from the pace at Toowoomba prior and is much better suited back to this level. Carries just 51kg with the claim and the step-up to the mile shouldn't be an issue. Sure to take plenty of stopping. EXPLOSIVE POWER (2) is a danger building on his second-up placing over 1415m at Ballina. The inside gate isn't ideal for him, but he's won over this trip and will finish hard. MISHANI IMPACT (4) won his maiden well over this trip at the Sunshine Coast and then dropped back to 1400m at Beaudesert in a 65 and didn't feature at big odds. Expect a better effort running into it late. AVERRED (8) brings a win and a near miss, both from Kilcoy over 1400m. In the mix with luck skipping across the wide barrier.
